[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":293},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":268,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":277},"\u002Fother\u002F20211013\u002F4225269670\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":250,"date":251,"description":252,"extension":253,"lang":254,"meta":255,"navigation":256,"path":257,"readingMinutes":258,"seo":259,"standalone":260,"stem":261,"tags":262,"tldr":264,"updated":265,"url":266,"__hash__":267},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id.md","How to Find Your Discord ID (Desktop + Mobile)","5520692674",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":238},"minimark",[11,20,25,28,32,40,48,52,55,62,69,72,98,101,105,108,113,120,125,136,141,156,161,165,168,173,179,184,190,196,202,205,211,217,223,229,235],[12,13,16],"callout",{"title":14,"type":15},"Note","note",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Your Discord ID is the unique numeric identifier for your account — a string of digits that never changes. To find yours, turn on Developer Mode in User Settings → Advanced, then click the \"⋯\" next to your avatar in My Account and pick \"Copy User ID\".",[21,22,24],"h2",{"id":23},"intro","Intro",[17,26,27],{},"I was building a Discord Bot recently and noticed something kind of annoying: Discord makes it weirdly fiddly to find your own User ID, and a lot of people end up grabbing the wrong thing. So this post walks through how to actually get it, with the mobile flow included.",[21,29,31],{"id":30},"whats-a-discord-id","What's a Discord ID?",[17,33,34,35,39],{},"First, let's sort out what a Discord ID actually is. Basically, your Discord ID is the ",[36,37,38],"strong",{},"unique identifier"," for your account. It never changes — which is why some services and bots will ask you to fill it in.",[17,41,42,43,47],{},"It's a long string of digits. Mine, for example, is ",[44,45,46],"code",{},"300879849289940992"," — that's my Discord ID.",[21,49,51],{"id":50},"the-wrong-things-people-grab","The wrong things people grab",[17,53,54],{},"If you're new to Discord, you might think the two highlighted bits below are your User ID (the arrows show what I mean):",[17,56,57],{},[58,59],"img",{"alt":60,"src":61},"User info","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426203841.png",[17,63,64,65,68],{},"That string \"",[36,66,67],{},"isray_notarray","\" isn't your Discord ID — it's just your username.",[17,70,71],{},"Discord actually has three different things going on here:",[73,74,75,86,92],"ul",{},[76,77,78,81,82,85],"li",{},[36,79,80],{},"Display Name",": This is the name shown to other people on Discord. Mine is set to \"",[44,83,84],{},"Ray ®","\", so that's what shows up.",[76,87,88,91],{},[36,89,90],{},"Username",": A handle you use to log in or be tagged. It's editable, so it's not a reliable identifier.",[76,93,94,97],{},[36,95,96],{},"User ID",": The unique identifier for your account — never changes, which is what services usually want.",[17,99,100],{},"So next we'll go through how to actually get the User ID — first on desktop, then on mobile.",[21,102,104],{"id":103},"turning-on-developer-mode","Turning on Developer Mode",[17,106,107],{},"Whether you're on desktop or mobile, step one is the same: turn on Developer Mode. This unlocks some extra info in the UI, like the option to copy User IDs and Channel IDs.",[109,110,112],"h3",{"id":111},"desktop","Desktop",[17,114,115,116,119],{},"Click \"",[36,117,118],{},"User Settings","\" at the bottom of the sidebar to open settings:",[17,121,122],{},[58,123],{"alt":118,"src":124},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426204558.png",[17,126,127,128,131,132,135],{},"In the left sidebar, find \"",[36,129,130],{},"Advanced","\" and toggle on \"",[36,133,134],{},"Developer Mode","\":",[17,137,138],{},[58,139],{"alt":134,"src":140},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426204726.png",[17,142,143,144,147,148,151,152,155],{},"Now go back to \"",[36,145,146],{},"My Account","\". You'll see a \"",[36,149,150],{},"⋯","\" next to your name — click it, and \"",[36,153,154],{},"Copy User ID","\" shows up. Click it and your User ID is on your clipboard.",[17,157,158],{},[58,159],{"alt":154,"src":160},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426205018.png",[109,162,164],{"id":163},"mobile","Mobile",[17,166,167],{},"The mobile flow also needs Developer Mode on. I'll use iOS as the example, but Android should be basically the same.",[17,169,170,171,135],{},"Open the app, tap your avatar in the bottom nav to open \"",[36,172,118],{},[17,174,175],{},[58,176],{"alt":177,"src":178},"Mobile User Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8658.jpg",[17,180,181,182,135],{},"Scroll down and find \"",[36,183,130],{},[17,185,186],{},[58,187],{"alt":188,"src":189},"Mobile Advanced","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8660.PNG",[17,191,192,193,195],{},"Toggle \"",[36,194,134],{},"\" on:",[17,197,198],{},[58,199],{"alt":200,"src":201},"Mobile Developer Mode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8661.PNG",[17,203,204],{},"Now go into any channel and send a message:",[17,206,207],{},[58,208],{"alt":209,"src":210},"Mobile send message","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8662.jpg",[17,212,213,214,135],{},"Tap your own avatar — a menu pops up. Tap \"",[36,215,216],{},"...",[17,218,219],{},[58,220],{"alt":221,"src":222},"Mobile menu","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8663.PNG",[17,224,225,226,228],{},"And \"",[36,227,154],{},"\" shows up. Tap it and the ID is copied:",[17,230,231],{},[58,232],{"alt":233,"src":234},"Mobile Copy User ID","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8664.PNG",[17,236,237],{},"That's how to find your Discord ID. Hope it helps.",{"title":239,"searchDepth":240,"depth":240,"links":241},"",2,[242,243,244,245],{"id":23,"depth":240,"text":24},{"id":30,"depth":240,"text":31},{"id":50,"depth":240,"text":51},{"id":103,"depth":240,"text":104,"children":246},[247,249],{"id":111,"depth":248,"text":112},3,{"id":163,"depth":248,"text":164},"Misc","2021-10-13 13:12:46","I was building a Discord Bot recently and noticed that finding your own Discord User ID is weirdly fiddly — and a lot of people get the wrong thing. So this post walks through how to grab it correctly, including the mobile flow.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id","2",{"title":6,"description":252},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id",[263,134,164],"Discord",null,"2026-05-12 09:00:00","\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F","HE6BbQqrmnBFqntRLtMOEfzN7prwH2hYIXvyVuZT3rE",{"newer":269,"older":273},{"url":270,"title":271,"date":272},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F22\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-02-architecture-overview\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (2) — Architecture Overview","2021-10-22 21:11:08",{"url":274,"title":275,"date":276},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F11\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-01-intro-and-setup\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (1) — Nuxt.js & Setup","2021-10-11 16:16:35",[278,283,288],{"url":279,"title":280,"date":281,"readingMinutes":282},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F07\u002F10\u002F100-day-body-recomposition-experiment\u002F","My 100-Day Body Recomposition Experiment, as a Software Engineer","2026-07-10 09:53:56","23",{"url":284,"title":285,"date":286,"readingMinutes":287},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":289,"title":290,"date":291,"readingMinutes":292},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",1784087334181]